bSnvI7q840AhxMBwwBmniQJ3.text: This library allows to work with sprite sheets organized in a regular array. Packaging many sprites into a single image is a very efficient way of dealing with large number of sprites.

Let's also create a picture that contains numbers that we will use as our sprite sheet.

f62rkZvdMMaoAuDsJ4RzoCm5.text: The library works with a single picture. Call `initialize` with the board, picture and number of rows and columns.

LslZdUmHjPAUedXMGNj74qv2.text: Did you get the number of columns, rows correctly? You can use the `draw grid` functionality to check where the sprites are cut.

eEamC4iH31odsqjBpLhhah6M.text: Call 'create sprite` to create a picture sprite that displays the sprite at a particular row and column.
Call `create sprite` to create a picture sprite that displays the sprite at a particular row and column.

m2asXkLeU0DI4HJaEqhM3Pyb.text: You can use the `set sprite picture` action to dynamically change which sprite cell is displayed on a sprite created by `create sprite`. This allows to easily cycle through images and create animations.

m2asXkLeU0DI4HJaEqhM3Pyb.text: You can use the `set sprite picture` action to dynamically change which sprite cell is displayed on a sprite created by `create sprite`.

XKqNz4niVLv2dA8JaF2TCriL.text: By changing the picture of a sprite, you can create animated characters. This is a classic technique used in game to create animations at a low computational cost.

l6O4yw2WPTsog8jeFlXx44gV.text: Search for the `sprite sheet animations` library to animate your sprites.

app.comment: Library to work with sprite sheets and animate them.

M1M4gm1En2tF9l7eM97meLMQ.text: Each sprite sheet has to be registered with a unique id. The `sheet id` will be used in other calls to identify that sprite sheet.
Each sprite sheet has to be registered with a unique id. The `sheet id` will be used in other calls to identify that sprite sheet. You can register multiple sprite sheets with this library.

The `create animation` action will create a picture sprite that cycles through the sprite cells, from left to right, top to bottom.

aoNMS3Ly3McehZhrdEvumjMM.text: `loops` controls how many times the animation is played. If `loops` is negative, the animation goes on forever. If `loops` is positive, the animation runs until the number of loops is achieved; then the sprite is deleted.

Create a fresh animated sprite from the `sheet id` sprite sheet. The animation runs for `duration` seconds, `loops` times. If `loops` is negative, the animation loops forever. If `loops` is positive, the animation will stop and the sprite will be deleted. The sprite cells are enumerated left to right, top to bottom.
